description: The Election Commission released the final voter turnout percentages for the first and second phases, which were 66.1% and 66.7% respectively, a few days after the polling was completed. This also happened on a day when opposition parties raised concerns about the delay in releasing the data to the public. In 2019, the voter turnout was 69.4% in the first phase and 69.2% in the second phase.
title: Final EC figures put Phase 1 turnout at 66.1%, 66.7% voted in Phase 2
HC allows couple for IVF despite man crossing age bar of 55

description: Income tax authorities confiscated 50 lakh rupees from a passenger from Delhi at Biju Patnaik International Airport in Bhubaneswar on Tuesday. Airport authorities mentioned that they oversee every chartered flight and the passengers on board. The information will be shared with the chief electoral officer and district election officers. According to the guidelines of the Election Commission, they are monitoring individuals arriving on chartered flights.

description: The Madhya Pradesh high court dismissed a plea by Congress’s Moti Singh Patel on Tuesday. Moti Singh Patel wanted his candidature to be accepted as the party nominee for Lok Sabha elections after the official candidate Akshay Kanti Bam pulled out and joined BJP on Monday. The district election office rejected Patel’s candidacy during the scrutiny on April 25.
title: After Indore candidate’s exit, HC junks Cong ‘substitute’s’ plea to contest

description: PM Narendra Modi's “bhatakti aatma” barb alluding to Sharad Pawar at successive campaign rallies in Maharashtra led the NCP (SP) chief to declare on Tuesday that he was “indeed a restless soul seeking to alleviate the pain of distressed farmers and citizens struggling to cope with high inflation”. State NCP (SP) president Jayant Patil said at a rally in Baramati that Modi would realise the outcome of mocking “Maharashtracha aatma” (soul of Maharashtra) on the day votes are counted.
title: Am a ‘bhatakti aatma’ for distressed farmers: Pawar retorts to PM Modi's barb

description: High courts face judge appointment challenges with 171 vacancies, impacting case pendency. Delayed HC collegium recommendations contribute to backlog. Minister Meghwal highlights slow process. SC collegium reviews candidates, involving Intelligence Bureau in selections."}
title: 327 judge posts in 25 HCs, or 29% of total, are lying vacant

description: A day after alluding to him as a “bhatakti aatma” (wandering soul) who spooks even his family members’ plans because he couldn’t fulfil his, PM Narendra Modi resumed his tirade against NCP (SP) chief Sharad Pawar on Tuesday with a call to show the “kaddaavar neta” (political stalwart) his place for repeatedly failing his voters.
title: In Maha’s sugar belt, Modi vs Pawar battle enters a not-so-sweet territory

description: Champat Rai, the general secretary of Shri Ram Janmabhoomi Teerth Kshetra Trust, refuted the claim made by Congress leader Rahul Gandhi that President Droupadi Murmu was not invited to the consecration of Ram Lalla’s idol at the Ayodhya temple because she is a tribal. Referring to Rahul’s allegation reported in this daily from Gandhinagar, Rai said they are “completely false, baseless and misleading”.

description: Gujarat Congress MLA Jignesh Mevani’s personal assistant (PA) and an AAP functionary were arrested on Tuesday on charges of sharing a deep-fake video of Union home minister Amit Shah about a purported promise “to end reservations for SCs, STs and OBCs” if BJP returns to office at the Centre.
title: Jignesh Mevani’s PA, AAP district chief held over Amit Shah deepfake video

description: Sex video tapes involving Prajwal Revanna surfaced from a dispute with aide Karthik over land in Holenarsipura. Karthik sought help from G Devarajegowda, leading to legal action against media. Obscene videos circulated before election in Hassan.

description: A Delhi court dismissed the second regular bail plea that was filed by former deputy chief minister Manish Sisodia in the money laundering and corruption cases related to the now scrapped liquor policy of 2021-22. The court of special judge Kaveri Baweja rejected the bail requests in the CBI and ED cases, mentioning that it was not the appropriate stage for it.

description: Amit Shah and BJP condemn sexual abuse involving Prajwal Revanna. Chandrasekhar lauds JD(S) for suspending him. BJP criticizes Karnataka govt's inaction on the matter, emphasizing zero tolerance for crimes against women.

description: Supreme Court on Tuesday said Enforcement Directorate would have to give an explanation on the timing of Delhi CM Arvind Kejriwal’s arrest, which was carried out just before general elections, and observed that the gap between initiation of proceedings in the alleged Delhi excise scam case and his arrest was “bothering” the court.

description: NCW calls for prompt action against Prajwal Revanna amid sexual abuse allegations. Congress questions Centre's silence, seeks protection for complainants. NCW condemns the acts and urges decisive action by authorities.

Legal issues escalated as Uttarakhand suspended 14 product licenses following a case filed by the Indian Medical Association in the SC, demanding drug formulas amidst an IMA case on misleading ads.

description: Former special secretary Manoj Soni arrested by ED in Chhattisgarh rice scam. ITS officer, Soni, placed under ED custody after questioning at ACB office. Presented before special PMLA court judge, remanded in 5 days’ custody. ED searched Soni's premises, Rice Millers Association. Alleged kickbacks by MARKFED.

description: Bank loans to the services and agriculture sectors were the primary contributors to the 20% increase in credit growth in FY24. Both sectors experienced growth of over 20%, as reported by the RBI. Although the rate of credit growth towards large industries more than doubled in FY24 (7%) compared to the previous year (3.1%), it still remained slow, leading to a continued decrease in market share.

description: On Tuesday, the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) tightened regulations for mutual funds to prevent front-running and price manipulation. Sebi will issue general guidelines for this, while the Association of Mutual Funds in India (Amfi), the industry trade body, will develop detailed guidelines, as stated in a release from the regulator. This action was prompted by multiple instances of front-running in fund companies.

description: India's continuous efforts to enhance its air and missile defense systems include the development and deployment of various indigenous and imported defense systems to safeguard its airspace against diverse aerial threats.

description: KYC registration entities, known as KRAs in the market, stated on Tuesday that out of approximately 11 crore investors under Sebi’s regulatory oversight, around 1.3 crore accounts are currently ‘on hold’ (indicating that these investors are unable to carry out transactions in stocks, MFs, and commodities using these KYCs) due to non-compliance with Sebi regulations for various reasons.

description: South India and east/northeast India experienced extreme heat in April, breaking records. Cities like Bengaluru, Kolkata, and Mumbai saw high temperatures. The entire South recorded an average maximum temperature of around 37.2 degrees Celsius and Bengaluru witnessed its hottest April. The heat wave is expected to continue in eastern India till May 2.

description: Benchmark indices sensex and Nifty closed lower on Tuesday because there was a selloff in banking and IT shares in the last hour of the session amidst a mixed trend in global markets. The Sensex dropped by 189 points to reach a closing value of 74,483. The index started with an increase and continued to rise by 440 points, reaching a peak of 75,111 during the day's trading.

description: UP school principal transforms classroom into a pool to combat low attendance in summer, attracting 65 students at Model Primary School in Tirwa's Mahsaunapur village through innovative thinking and community involvement.

description: The Godrejs have reached a settlement to split the Rs 59,000-crore ($7 billion) locks-to-land development group to “better align ownership in acknowledgement of the differing visions of the family members”. Adi Godrej and his brother Nadir Godrej will have full ownership of the five publicly listed companies of the Godrej Group, which include Godrej Consumer Products, Godrej Properties, Godrej Industries, Godrej Agrovet, and Astec Lifesciences.

description: Solicitor General Mehta extensively quotes B R Ambedkar on economic democracy, Article 39(b), and social welfare state alignment in court, emphasizing the importance of various economic democracy forms and the Constituent Assembly debate.

description: The report by The Washington Post alleged that top Indian officials, including former RAW chief Samant Goel, were involved in the Pannun murder-for-hire plot. The report made 'unwarranted' and 'unsubstantiated claims' on a serious matter, as stated by the Indian government on Tuesday in its initial response to the story.

description: India saved $7.9B in 2023-24 oil imports by purchasing discounted Russian crude, impacting deficit. Potential $101-104B oil bill for 2024-25. Russian crude share surged to 36%.

description: The Central Administrative Tribunal (CAT) has nullified the compulsory retirement of IPS officer Gurjinder Pal Singh from service and directed his reinstatement with all related benefits within a period of four weeks. The officer from the 1991 batch was serving as ADG in Chhattisgarh when he was retired involuntarily from service following a raid by the anti-corruption bureau (ACB).

description: Government's open market sale of wheat ensures supply stability, reduced FCI borrowings, and aided welfare schemes. FCI aims for 300-310 lakh tonnes procurement this year. description: As Mumbai Indians succumbed to their seventh defeat of the season, this time against Lucknow Super Giants, skipper Hardik Pandya said loss of early wickets led to their down fall at the Ekana. After being put in to bat by KL Rahul, MI found themselves tottering at 28 for four after powerplay with pacers Mohsin Khan, Marcus Stoinis and Naveen-ul-Haq doing the early damage. Rohit Sharma (4), Suryakumar Yadav (10), Tilak Varma (7) and Hardik (0) all fell cheaply as Ishan Kishan (32) and Nehal Wadhera (46) and Tim David (35) somehow took them to a par total.

description: With this win, LSG jumped to third place in the standings with 12 points in 10 games, which consisted of six wins and four losses. Batting first, MI posted a total of 144 for 7, with Nehal Wadhera top-scoring with 46 runs. Tim David and Ishan Kishan contributed with unbeaten innings of 35 and 32 runs, respectively. In reply, LSG successfully chased down the target in 19.2 overs. The standout performer for LSG was Marcus Stoinis, who played a crucial knock of 62 runs off 45 balls.

description: Former England international cricketer Monty Panesar has announced that he is running for the Workers Party of Britain led by George Galloway in the upcoming UK general election. His aim is to defeat the long-standing Labour MP Virendra Sharma, who has represented the Ealing Southall constituency since 2007. Galloway, who is well-liked by Muslims for his supportive stance on Palestine and opposition to Israel, introduced 500 candidates.

description: The founding family of the 127-year-old Godrej Group, which operates in various sectors such as soaps, home appliances, and real estate, has come to an agreement to divide the conglomerate. This loss severely impacted the five-time champions' chances of securing a top-four spot, leaving them in ninth place in the standings with only 6 points.

description: US universities witness protests against Gaza war, while a Harvard CAPS-Harris survey indicates strong American support for Israel over Hamas. Demonstrations call for boycotts of Israeli-linked companies, leading to clashes with campus security.
title: '80% Americans support Israel despite pro-Palestine protests'

description: ​​Justice Hima Kohli and Justice Ahsanuddin Amanullah's bench expressed dissatisfaction with the explanation provided by the body, noting that it seemed the licensing authority only acted in compliance with the law after the Supreme Court's order on April 10. "Be honest to the court if you want sympathy and compassion...," the bench observed.
title: Patanjali ads: SC pulls up Uttarakhand State Licensing Authority

description: Seven Maoists, including 2 women, killed in Chhattisgarh encounter. Casualties may rise in ongoing operation. STF, DRG recover bodies, AK 47, ammo, explosives. Police await further details.
title: 8 Maoists killed in encounter with security forces in Bastar

description: Obsession with Instagram Reels in Noida led to physical confrontations among four girls at Biodiversity Park. Video posted by X user on Saturday shows police officers not intervening. Viewers' humorous responses flooded the comment section.
title: Noida catfight: Girls punching, slapping, pulling each other's hair

description: Hayden raised doubts over Kohli's ability to bat in the middle overs on the slow and low wickets expected in US and West Indies, the co-hosts of the June 2 to 29 tournament. There were doubts raised over Virat's place in the T20 World Cup squad before the start of the ongoing IPL season, but the Indian legend's bat has silenced all doubters, amassing 500 runs in 10 matches.
title: 'Will Virat Kohli win you the T20 World Cup?'

description: Hayden raised doubts over Kohli's ability to bat in the middle overs on the slow and low wickets expected in US and West Indies, the co-hosts of the June 2 to 29 tournament. title: 'Will Virat Kohli win you the T20 World Cup?'

description: Actor-producer Harman Baweja, known for his recent role in Hansal Mehta's "Scoop," welcomes a baby girl with wife Sasha Ramchandani in March, marking their second child. Despite keeping their personal life private, the couple embraces parenthood after the birth of their son in December 2022. Their union follows a discreet relationship and marriage in 2021.
title: Harman Baweja and wife welcome a baby girl

description: JD(S) suspends Prajwal Revanna amid sexual harassment case. HD Kumaraswamy clarifies suspension until investigation concludes. Case involves IPC sections, SIT investigation team.
title: Sex tapes: JD(S) suspends Deve Gowda's grandson Prajwal Revanna

description: Elon Musk dismisses two senior Tesla executives: The report by The Information cites an email from Musk to senior managers. The report states that Rebecca Tinucci, head of Tesla's Supercharger division, and Daniel Ho, leader of the new vehicles program, will depart on Tuesday morning.
title: 'Musk lays off Tesla senior execs; plans to dismiss hundreds more'

description: PFRDA's guidelines impact NPS PoPs' fee structure, introducing persistency charges. Security upgrades include Aadhaar-based authentication, and nodal offices must verify documents thoroughly for exit/withdrawal requests in the CRA system, ensuring accuracy and adherence to guidelines.
title: NPS subscribers: New charges and security measures

description: Former Indian cricketer Gautam Gambhir discussed Rohit Sharma's remarkable journey during his 37th birthday celebration. Gambhir reminisced about a series in Sri Lanka where Sharma faced criticism for low scores. Gambhir predicted Sharma would dominate world cricket, which has come true, and highlighted the importance of understanding and embracing his talent.
title: 'You're going to dominate': Gambhir recalls words to young Rohit

description: Admiral Dinesh Kumar Tripathi, on Tuesday took charge as the 26th Navy chief after R Hari Kumar retired from service. Dinesh K Tripathi, earlier served as the director-general of naval operations and the flag officer commanding-in-chief of the Western Naval Command. An official announcement was made by the government on April 19.
title: Admiral Dinesh Tripathi takes charge as Navy chief

description: Former Australia captain Michael Clarke emphasized teamwork over individual brilliance for winning major tournaments. He suggests Mumbai Indians' camp is divided, hindering effective collaboration. Despite proven match-winners, MI's inconsistent performance raises doubts about playoff qualification. Clarke acknowledges that individual impact could work sometimes but stresses the necessity of team cohesion for tournament success.
title: IPL 2024: 'Mumbai Indians camp is divided'
Raghav Chadha 'might have lost eyesight': Saurabh Bharadwaj

description: Expensive street food at Mumbai airport costs ₹333 per plate, sparking netizens' debate on high prices. In a similar incident, a restaurant sold dosas and buttermilk for ₹600-₹620.
title: Mumbai airport's Rs 333 pani puri draws mixed reactions
'Dog friendly, child free': Sign outside England pub sparks debate

description: Amit Shah criticized Congress for spreading fake videos, accused Rahul Gandhi of degrading politics. Kharge criticized BJP for hate speech. Shah questioned Congress's inaction in Karnataka case. He questioned Gandhi's confidence in avoiding traditional seats in Uttar Pradesh. Responding to this, Congress president Mallikarjun Kharge said that the BJP has "expertise" to "make videos and defame people through social media."
title: Rahul working to take level of politics to new low: Amit Shah

description: Former India cricketer Aakash Chopra criticized Delhi Capitals skipper Rishabh Pant's batting approach during an Indian Premier League match against Kolkata Knight Riders. Chopra criticized Pant's reckless shot selection and repeated erratic play at the crease, leading to his dismissal. Chopra's comments sparked criticism of Pant's performance and the team's situation.
title: 'Can't bat like that': Ex-India batter slams Pant's approach

description: Delhi Capitals bat first against Kolkata Knight Riders, resulting in a below-par total of 153/9. KKR secured second spot in the IPL points table with seven-wicket win at the Eden Gardens. Former India cricketer Aakash Chopra expressed surprise at DC's decision, noting that teams batting first have struggled to secure victories in Kolkata.
title: 'If Ganguly couldn't read...': Ex-player slams DC's decision to bat first

description: A German Shepherd attacked a girl in a Ghaziabad society, sparking concerns about pet dogs in public areas. The family filed an FIR, leading to the UP government banning 23 ferocious dog breeds.
title: German Shepherd attacks child riding tricycle in Ghaziabad

description: Lucknow Super Giants skipper KL Rahul discussed his T20 cricket evolution, crediting insights from Virat Kohli, AB de Villiers, and Kane Williamson. Time at Royal Challengers Bangalore was pivotal, observing their preparation. Interactions with Williamson at Sunrisers Hyderabad were influential. Rahul's IPL 2024 form, with 378 runs in nine matches, showcases his prowess, both with the bat and as captain.
title: 'Utna baat nahi karta tha but...': KL on Kohli, ABD's influence

description: Vadodara's crocodile mascot, under Arjunsinh Chauhan's leadership, promotes voter engagement through comics, including Genie-themed ones. The initiative also educates on election rules and timing, enhancing voter awareness.
title: Snap to it: Crocodiles urge Barodians to vote

description: Royal Challengers Bengaluru net bowler Mukesh Kumar has gained attention after a viral video showcasing his striking resemblance to Indian cricket team star Jasprit Bumrah in bowling action. Kumar, previously associated with Gujarat Titans, has captivated fans and pundits with his impeccable imitation.
title: Watch: Net bowler impresses with Bumrah-esque action

description: The report claimed that RAW member Vikram Yadav purportedly directed a contracted hit squad to assassinate Gurpatwant Singh Pannun, a separatist based in the United States. The report suggested that US intelligence agencies have concluded that the mission aimed at Pannun received approval from then-chief of RAW Samant Goel. It further notes that Yadav was reassigned to the Central Reserve Police Force (CRPF) after the failed Pannun operation came to light last year.
title: 'Unsubstantial imputations': India on US report naming RAW agent in plot to kill Pannun

description: Rather than focusing solely on IPL performers, selectors might need to prioritize maintaining the freshness of their player pool following the intense two-month IPL cricket season. The 2009, 2010 and 2021 T20 World Cups were played soon after the IPL. In each instance, India failed to reach the semifinals, raising concerns about player fatigue and performance.
title: T20 WC squad: Should selectors get swayed by IPL form?

description: Rather than focusing solely on IPL performers, selectors might need to prioritize maintaining the freshness of their player pool following the intense two-month IPL cricket season. The 2009, 2010 and 2021 T20 World Cups were played soon after the IPL. In each instance, India failed to reach the semifinals, raising concerns about player fatigue and performance.
title: T20 WC squad: Should selectors get swayed by IPL form?

description: Stock market today: BSE Sensex and Nifty50, the Indian equity benchmark indices, resumed their rally on Tuesday after a strong show on Monday. BSE Sensex moves up 100 points and Nifty50 was above 22,650.
title: Sensex up 100 points near 74,700; Nifty above 22,650

description: In his inaugural address on the floor of the National Assembly (NA) following the 2024 elections, JUI-F chief and Pakistani opposition leader, Maulana Fazlur Rehman drew a sharp contrast with India, asserting, "India is dreaming of becoming a superpower, while we are begging to avoid bankruptcy. Who is responsible for this?"
title: 'Pak begs to avoid bankruptcy while India aiming to be superpower'

description: Uttarakhand suspends 14 products' manufacturing licenses by Patanjali Ayurveda ltd and Divya Pharmacy due to repeated violations of the Drugs and Magic Remedies Act. The state licensing authority informed in an affidavit that the cancellation order was issued for "repeated violations" of the Drugs and Magic Remedies (Objectionable Advertisements) Act, 1954.
title: U'khand suspends licenses of 14 Patanjali products; check list

description: IIT Madras researchers identify Indian Ocean and Bay of Bengal as carbon sequestration sites, utilizing gas hydrate crystals to capture CO2 in eco-friendly structures. The research aims to aid in achieving India's decarbonization goals while preserving marine ecology.
title: Bay of Bengal a carbon sink, says IIT-Madras study

description: Mount Ruang in Indonesia's North Sulawesi province erupted multiple times on Tuesday, prompting the evacuation of over 6,000 people and the closure of a nearby international airport. The eruptions, which began early in the morning, sent a column of ash more than five kilometers into the sky. Authorities reinstated a six-kilometer exclusion zone and warned of potential hazards such as incandescent rocks, hot clouds, and tsunamis.
title: Indonesia's Mount Ruang erupts again, forces evacuation

description: MI currently occupy the second-to-last position in the IPL standings among the ten competing teams. Head-to-head statistics indicate that LSG have consistently outperformed MI. But despite LSG having the statistical advantage, MI may come out all guns blazing as they are in a desperate situation, needing victories in all five of their remaining matches in the race to playoffs.
title: LSG vs MI: Will Mayank Yadav's pace make Mumbai hop?

description: Uttarakhand's Kumaon region battles severe forest fires amidst an 85% rainfall deficit in April. The crisis escalates with minimal precipitation, stark rainfall differences, and heightened concerns of intensified fires due to climate change impact.
title: Forest fires intensify amid Uttarakhand's driest April in 5 yrs

description: Sumit Panchal's suspicious death in Kota hostel prompts family to seek SIT probe. No suicide note found. Medical board conducts autopsy. Investigation ongoing into the unnatural death.
title: NEET aspirant from Rohtak dies by suicide in Kota

description: Kolkata Knight Riders secured a seven-wicket victory over Delhi Capitals after opener Phil Salt's 68-run innings. However, Axar Patel's sensational delivery to dismiss Salt, drawing comparisons to spin legends Srinivasaraghavan Venkataraghavan and Bishan Singh Bedi, sparked praise. Patel's precision and guile were on full display on the first ball of the ninth over, as he clean bowled Salt.
title: Watch: Axar's delivery draws comparison to spin legends

description: Anil Kumar celebrates daughter Urvi's divorce, defying stigma. Urvi faced dowry harassment, divorcing after 8 years with her husband, a computer engineer in Delhi, where they have a daughter.
title: Kanpur: Dad brings divorced daughter home with ‘band-baja’

description: Riya Rajgor and Avdhesh Dubey died falling off crowded trains. Riya was declared dead at Shastri Nagar Hospital. Commuters demand more trains from Dombivli and criticize slow metro work. The incidents highlight safety concerns.
title: 26-year-old falls to her death from packed local train in Mumbai

description: Vande Bharat Express faced technical issues at Surat station, causing delays and frustration among passengers. The lack of information and assistance from railway staff added to the ordeal, impacting scheduled meetings and causing a cascading effect on other trains.
title: Vande Bharat doors fail to open at Surat station

description: Dominant castes demand bigger piece of pie
title: Why caste quota remains a hot button issue in Karnataka politics

description: Nirmala Devi convicted for luring college girls into sexual favors by Srivilliputhur mahila court. V Murugan, S Karuppasamy acquitted. CB-CID involved. Sentence to be announced on Tuesday.
title: Ex-professor guilty of luring TN college students into sex

description: Fifty students from Maheshwari Vidhyapeeth escaped a potential accident when the drunk bus driver, Suresh Singh Rajput, was stopped by an alert Class 10 student in Althan. The school ensures no recurrence.
title: Surat: How alert students stopped vehicle and saved 50 lives

description: Bhopal officials introduce lucky draws with prizes like diamond rings to boost voter participation. Efforts include post-election mega draw and first voter felicitation. SVEEP ensures printed voter slips for all constituents.
title: Lucky you! Diamond ring for your vote in Bhopal

description: Kolkata Knight Riders secured a commanding seven-wicket victory over Delhi Capitals in an Indian Premier League match on Monday, thanks to Phil Salt's explosive batting. Former KKR skipper and current mentor Gautam Gambhir's social media post encapsulated the triumph, praising Salt's sensational knock and its pivotal role in KKR's victory.
title: 'Right amount of Salt': Gambhir celebrates Salt's heroics in style

description: Microsoft CEO Satya Nadella prioritizes cybersecurity amid criticism over handling attacks by China and Russia on US agencies. Company undergoes major security update, placing security above all else.
title: Microsoft CEO says company 'doubling down' on this 'no. 1 priority'

description: Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah actor, Gurucharan Singh Sodhi, is missing. Co-stars, friends express concern. Last seen in Delhi, heading to Mumbai. Actor's father filed a missing person complaint. Police investigating the case.
title: Actor Gurucharan Singh missing: Co-stars pray for safe return

description: Revanth Reddy accuses Modi and Shah of using various agencies against opposition. Modi labeled a cobra for farm laws retraction. Notices served over doctored video. Campaigning in Karnataka during Delhi police visit.
title: Shah fake video: Not scared of notice, says T'gana CM Reddy

description: Voters in Baramati face indecisiveness over Pawars' town, ensuring a contest. Flexes of Supriya Tai and Sunetra Tai adorn autorickshaws. Sharad Pawar and Ajit Pawar's jingles add spice to the battle in the Baramati Lok Sabha seat.
title: Keen contest in Baramati after decades: Party split divides voters

description: Shah Rukh Khan and Sourav Ganguly shared a special moment during the IPL match between Kolkata Knight Riders and Delhi Capitals. Ganguly, who served as KKR's star and inaugural captain in 2008, now serves as the director of cricket for Delhi Capitals. The nostalgic reunion added to the highly anticipated match.
title: 'Hugs & kisses': SRK reunites with Ganguly at Eden - Watch

description: Goa Crime Branch Police arrested 16 individuals suspected of being involved in an Indian Premier League cricket betting racket. 15 from Gujarat and one from Uttar Pradesh were arrested in Porvorim, North Goa, after facilitating bets during the IPL cricket match between Sunrisers Hyderabad and Chennai Super Kings.
title: Goa Police bust IPL betting racket, apprehend 16

description: Columbia University started suspending activists supporting Palestine who declined to remove a tent camp on its campus in New York City after the prestigious Ivy League institution announced a deadlock in discussions aimed at resolving the divisive protest. University President Nemat Minouche Shafik mentioned in a statement that despite days of discussions between student organizers and academic leaders.
title: Columbia suspends pro-Palestinian protesters after encampment talks stall

description: Rohit Sharma, a renowned cricketer and Team India captain, celebrated his 37th birthday on Tuesday. He made India debut in 2007, Sharma has a remarkable career spanning over a decade and a half. He has become known as one of the finest batsmen of his generation. His grace and power have earned him a reputation worldwide.
title: Happy Birthday Rohit! 'Hitman' of Indian cricket turns 37

description: PM Modi revealed on Monday the untold story of how he ensured Pakistan was the first to officially hear about the 2019 Balakot airstrike, linking it to BJP-governed “new India’s policy of looking an adversary in the eye and speaking the truth rather than resorting to stealth”, reports Gururaj Jamkhandi.
title: ‘Modi fights from front, told Pak about Balakot strike before world knew’

description: A report in the Washington Post, a newspaper based in the United States, has alleged that Vikram Yadav, an officer from the Research and Analysis Wing, directed a hired hit team to assassinate Gurpatwant Singh Pannun, a Khalistani separatist based in the US. Last year, authorities in the United States indicted Nikhil Gupta, an Indian national, for the conspiracy.
title: US report names RAW man involved in alleged plot to take out Pannun
'Can’t levy interest on loan amounts not received': RBI to Banks

description: The Ministry of External Affairs summoned the Canadian Deputy High Commissioner on Monday and expressed strong opposition to the open chanting of separatist pro-Khalistan slogans at an event where Canadian PM Justin Trudeau was speaking. Trudeau spoke at a 'Khalsa Day' event in Toronto where banners saying 'Modi wanted' were displayed, causing concern among Indian intelligence officials, according to sources.
title: India fumes at Trudeau taking part in pro-Khalistan event

description: Arrest of BJP member at Madurai airport for offering ganja packets to M K Stalin. Taken into custody under NDPS Act. Chief minister travels to Kodaikanal with family.
title: BJP man attempts to meet TN CM Stalin with ganja, held
BSE’s stock crashes 13% after Sebi seeks fee difference of around 165 crore

description: Uttarakhand continued to deal with the persistent forest fire problem on Monday. The state reported 47 new incidents, burning approximately 78 hectares of forest land. The majority of these fires affected the Kumaon region, with 30 incidents destroying an area of 51 hectares. Garhwal also recorded 16 incidents, impacting 25 hectares, with one incident burning 1.5 hectares of protected forests.
title: 47 new fires raze 78 hectares forest land across state

description: The UGC-NET exam has been rescheduled to take place on June 18 instead of the previously planned date of June 16, as notified by the National Testing Agency. The decision to postpone the exam was made in response to concerns raised by aspirants regarding the clash of dates between the UPSC Prelims and NET exams.
title: UGC-NET exam postponed to June 18
